nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div style=3D"=
margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span style=3D=
"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">I have read through the c=
oncerns raised by your customer in the email below.&nbsp; I think it would b=
e useful for us to clarify the involvement of ASURNZ, our independence to To=
wer Insurance, our experience, and our approach to determining remediation r=
equired for damage caused by fire, heat, chemicals, and smoke resulting from=
 fire related events.</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div><di=
v><div style=3D"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif=
;"><span style=3D"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</=
span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div style=3D"margin:=
 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><b><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fairness and participation</=
span></b><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div style=3D"mar=
gin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">ASURNZ operates as third-pa=
rty provider specialising in damage assessment and remediation, building pro=
duct and building system compliance, and legislative and regulatory requirem=
ents for building related matters.&nbsp; In these matters we also provide ex=
pert witness services to the Courts.&nbsp; Our customers include private bui=
lding owners (residential, commercial, and industrial), insurers, building c=
onsent authorities (including Auckland Council), and building product manufa=
cturers. As such we provide a service that is independent and impartial of T=
ower Insurance.</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div=
 style=3D"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><sp=
an style=3D"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Details from o=
ur site inspection, including relevant photo schedules are provided in our r=
eporting, however we understand that homeowners will often have property spe=
cific questions. We are happy to meet with your customer to go over our find=
ings, and to listen to and consider their concerns.</span><o:p></o:p></div><=
/div></div></div><div><div><div><div style=3D"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; f=
ont-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 10pt; font-family:=
 Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><d=
iv><div><div style=3D"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans=
-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fi=
re chemistry &amp; severity</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><d=
iv><div><div style=3D"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans=
-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">AS=
URNZ has extensive experience in the assessment and remediation of fire/smok=
e damaged buildings.&nbsp; In all building fires there is risk that material=
s affected by fire can contribute to or cause corrosion from airborne means (=
transfer via smoke and heat).&nbsp; However, corrosion and the potential for=
 corrosion of building components is readily assessable from visible inspect=
ion and reasonable testing.&nbsp; For example, corrosion on mild steel or ga=
lvanised steel components and aluminium components (painted or unpainted) wi=
ll manifest on exposed surfaces of those materials and are immediately appar=
ent on visual inspection.&nbsp; If no significant corrosion is present on su=
rfaces directly exposed to heat and smoke, as was the situation observed in y=
our customers dwelling, enclosed surfaces such as within wall or ceiling cav=
ities will be less affected and therefore will not suffer corrosion from fir=
e related fumes. &nbsp;In all situations for remediation we consider the fol=
lowing steps in order: cleaning; encapsulation (where cleaning alone is insu=
fficient and the product is not damaged or will not be damaged by cleaning);=
 and replacement (where neither cleaning nor encapsulation will provide effe=
ctive remediation).&nbsp; These steps also follow the same principles set ou=
t in the Institute of Inspection Cleaning, Restoration, and Certification (I=
ICRC) codes of practice.</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div>=
<div><div style=3D"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-se=
rif;"><span style=3D"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Howev=
er, as your customer has provided new information regarding the possible pre=
sence of pool chemicals, we suggest that we engage the services of Alexandra=
 Dalzell from Forensic Specialists to undertake testing for the presence of r=
esidual chemicals on selected surfaces throughout the dwelling.&nbsp; The ou=
tcomes of such testing will then be used to further inform the remediation s=
trategy and include, where appropriate, clearance testing post-repair.</span=
><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div><div><div style=3D"margin: 0cm=
; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-size=
: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Regarding structural matters, as th=
is is a timber framed residential building and the structure can be addresse=
d using the NZ Standard for timber framed buildings not requiring specific e=
ngineering design (NZS 3604:2011) there is no need for the involvement of a C=
PEng structural engineer.&nbsp; Further, as one of the authors of NZS 3604 a=
nd current chair of that standards development committee I provide ASURNZ wi=
th specialist timber and timber framing knowledge that few engineers have, i=
ncluding regarding the durability of timber and regulatory requirements that=
 relate to the repair of existing buildings.&nbsp; Also, the structural dama=
ge to timber members is readily apparent and relatively localised.&nbsp; In t=
his regard I do not believe there is any benefit to be gained by engaging a C=
PEng structural engineer.</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div=
><div><div style=3D"margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-s=
