sp; Similarly, the practice note from Auckland Council does not apply, and i=
n any case is not a regulatory or legislative requirement.&nbsp; Note that t=
he defining legislation is the Building Act 2004 (the Act).&nbsp; The Act ov=
errides any policy of a building consent authority.&nbsp; The provisions of t=
he Act make clear that a building consent is not required for the proposed r=
epairs to this dwelling.</span><o:p></o:p></div></div></div></div><div><div>=
