 to the briefings or either site inspection. I appreciate this may have been=
 an oversight, but it leaves me without visibility of the brief given to ASU=
RNZ and what they actually saw on the day.<br>To balance the process, I kind=
ly propose that Tower funds an independent insured-side assessment with me d=
irectly engaged; and that I am permitted a one-on-one session with ASURNZ, a=
